# Architecture

## Folder structure

```
features/<name>/
  data/        → datasources, models, repository impl
  domain/      → entities, repository contracts, use cases
  presentation/→ bloc, pages, widgets
  bindings/    → DI registration for the feature
```

## Data flow — never bypass

```
UI → Bloc → UseCase → Repository → Datasource → Database → Native APIs
```

| Layer | May call | Must NOT call |
|-------|----------|---------------|
| UI | Bloc | UseCase, Repository, Datasource |
| Bloc | UseCase | Repository, Datasource, DB |
| UseCase | Repository | Datasource, DB, API |
| RepositoryImpl | Datasource | UI, Bloc |
| Datasource | Database / API / Platform | UI, Bloc, UseCase |

## Dependency rule

- `presentation` → `domain` only
- `data` → `domain`
- `domain` has **no** Flutter or data-layer imports

## Use cases

- One class per action; name as verb: `GetDashboardUseCase`.
- Extend `UseCase<T, Params>` from `lib/core/usecase/`.

## Repositories

- Abstract contract in `domain/repository/`.
- Implementation in `data/repository/`.

## Feature workflow

Follow `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc` — implement in order:

`Requirement → Architecture → Folder Structure → Entities → Database → Repository → UseCases → Bloc → UI → Testing`

Do not skip steps or generate UI before lower layers exist.
